%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22British%20Prime%20minister%20announces%20ban%20on%20american%20XL%20bully%20dogs%20following%20fatal%20attacks%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694871875000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-103718136%2Cimgsize-580992.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fbritish-prime-minister-announces-ban-on-american-xl-bully-dogs-following-fatal-attacks%2Farticleshow%2F103718115.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TIMESOFINDIA.COM%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22BP%20boss%20who%20resigned%20over%20undisclosed%20relationships%20with%20colleagues%20ended%20his%20marriage%20by%20text%20message%2C%20says%20ex-wife%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222842%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Bernard%20Looney%20wearing%20a%20suit%20and%20tie%20whilst%20gazing%20into%20the%20distance%20%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F650590c7f05aa00019bd981c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221895%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBernard%20Looney%20was%20CEO%20of%20BP%20for%20more%20than%20three%20years.%3Cp%3EARUN%20SANKAR%2F%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EBernard%20Looney%20resigned%20as%20CEO%20of%20BP%20on%20Tuesday%20over%20undisclosed%20relationships%20with%20colleagues.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHis%20ex-wife%2C%20Jacqueline%20Hurst%2C%20wrote%20in%20her%202021%20book%20he%20ended%20their%20marriage%20in%20a%20text%20message.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20claimed%20that%20Looney%20only%20married%20her%20%26quot%3Bto%20get%20to%20the%20next%20level%20of%20seniority%20in%20the%20company.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20former%20wife%20of%20BP's%20CEO%20who%20abruptly%20resigned%20this%20week%20said%20he%20ended%20their%20marriage%20%26quot%3Bwithout%20warning%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bsuddenly%26quot%3B%20over%20a%20text%20message.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBernard%20Looney%20stepped%20down%20from%20the%20top%20of%20BP%2C%20one%20of%20the%20world's%20biggest%20oil%20and%20gas%20companies%2C%20on%20Tuesday%20night%20after%20admitting%20he%20hadn't%20disclosed%20close%20relationships%20with%20colleagues%20that%20had%20since%20come%20to%20light.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20ex-wife%2C%20Jacqueline%20Hurst%2C%20said%20in%20her%20book%20%26quot%3BHow%20To%20Do%20You%3A%20The%20Life%20Changing%20Art%20of%20Mastering%20Your%20Thoughts%20and%20Taking%20Control%20of%20Your%20Life%26quot%3B%20that%20Looney%20told%20her%20he%20was%20leaving%20her%20on%20a%20chat%20on%20the%20messaging%20platform%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Fwhatsapp%3Fr%3DUS%26IR%3DT%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWhatsApp%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20my%20husband%20ended%20our%20marriage%20suddenly%20and%20without%20warning%20via%20a%20WhatsApp%20message%2C%20I%20was%20naturally%20devastated%2C%26quot%3B%20Hurst%20wrote%20in%20the%20book%20published%20in%202021.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20learned%20later%20that%20he%20had%20only%20married%20me%20because%20he%20wanted%20to%20get%20to%20the%20next%20level%20of%20seniority%20in%20the%20company%20he%20worked%20at%20and%20he%20had%20to%20be%20seen%20to%20be%20married%2C%20in%20order%20to%20be%20given%20the%20promotion%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20author%20and%20life%20coach%2C%20who%20married%20Looney%20in%202017%2C%20said%20that%20the%20way%20he%20ended%20their%20marriage%20was%20%26quot%3Bunbelievable%26quot%3B.%20She%20also%20said%20it%20was%20an%20%26quot%3Bunexpected%20gift%26quot%3B%20that%20they%20divorced%20in%202019%2C%20three%20months%20before%20he%20became%20CEO%20of%20BP%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.standard.co.uk%2Fbusiness%2Fbp-turtle-bernard-looney-deepwater-profits-b1106769.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EEvening%20Standard%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ELooney%20resigned%20as%20CEO%20of%20BP%20after%20less%20than%20four%20years%20in%20the%20role.%20In%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bp.com%2Fen%2Fglobal%2Fcorporate%2Fnews-and-insights%2Fpress-releases%2Fbp-ceo-resigns.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Estatement%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20BP%20announced%20his%20departure%20following%20an%20investigation%20into%20his%20conduct%20and%20personal%20relationships%20with%20colleagues.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20said%20that%20the%20board%20was%20tipped%20off%20in%20May%202022%20about%20claims%20he'd%20had%20personal%20relationships%20with%20coworkers.%20In%20a%20review%20Looney%20%26quot%3Bdisclosed%20a%20small%20number%20of%20historical%20relationships%20with%20colleagues%20prior%20to%20becoming%20CEO.%26quot%3B%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThe%20company%20said%20Looney%20breached%20its%20code%20of%20conduct%2C%20but%20that%20it%20received%20%26quot%3Bfurther%20allegations%20of%20a%20similar%20nature%26quot%3B%20more%20recently.%20BP%20said%20it's%20now%20investigating%20those%20claims.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ELooney%20%26quot%3Bdid%20not%20provide%20details%20of%20all%20relationships%20and%20accepts%20he%20was%20obligated%20to%20make%20more%20complete%20disclosure%2C%26quot%3B%20per%20the%20statement.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2F65837ce0-57cd-4db6-8de7-af190c37f77c%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFinancial%20Times%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%20some%20in%20the%20oil%20industry%20had%20joked%20that%20dealing%20with%20the%20fallout%20of%20Looney's%20departure%20%26quot%3B%3Cspan%3Ecould%20be%20BP's%20biggest%20clean-up%20operation%20since%20the%20Gulf%20of%20Mexico%20oil%20spill%26quot%3B%20in%202010.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20the%20first%20sudden%20resignation%20by%20a%20BP%20CEO.%20In%20May%202007%20John%20Browne%20quit%20after%20a%20UK%20court%20lifted%20an%20injunction%20preventing%20a%20newspaper%20group%20from%20publishing%20details%20about%20his%20private%20life%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Farticle%2Fus-bp-ceo-idUSWLA811920070501%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EReuters%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeparately%2C%20another%20British%20executive%2C%20Steve%20Easterbrook%2C%20was%20ousted%20as%20global%20CEO%20of%20McDonald's%20in%202019%20following%20a%20relationship%20with%20a%20colleague%20that%20breached%20the%20company's%20code%20of%20conduct.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcDonald's%20then%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmcdonalds-files-lawsuit-against-former-ceo-steve-easterbrook-2020-8%3Fr%3DUS%26IR%3DT%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eaccused%20him%20in%20a%202020%20lawsuit%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20covering%20up%20relationships%20with%20three%20other%20coworkers%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmcdonalds-lawsuit-against-its-ex-ceo-bizarre-details-2020-8%3Fr%3DUS%26IR%3DT%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Esending%20nude%20photographs%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20his%20work%20email%20account.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBP%20and%20Looney%20didn't%20immediately%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment%20from%20Insider%2C%20made%20outside%20normal%20working%20hours.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbp-bernard-looney-ex-wife-said-he-ended-marriage-text-2023-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694871342000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F650591cfcd637c0019c64f42%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbp-bernard-looney-ex-wife-said-he-ended-marriage-text-2023-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Bernard%20Looney%20abruptly%20resigned%20from%20BP%20this%20week%20after%20admitting%20he%20failed%20to%20disclose%20relationships%20with%20colleagues%20at%20the%20oil%20giant.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jmann%40insider.com%20(Jyoti%20Mann)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbp-bernard-looney-ex-wife-said-he-ended-marriage-text-2023-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22With%20'A%20Haunting%20in%20Venice'%2C%20the%20Director%20Goes%20in%20More%20for%20Mood%20and%20Atmosphere%20Rather%20Than%20Glamour%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F16171626%2Fimage-1321.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20%3Cem%3EA%20Haunting%20in%20Venice%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20one%20can%20almost%20immediately%20tell%20that%20director%2Factor%20Kenneth%20Branagh%20intends%20to%20class%20things%20up%2C%20especially%20after%20the%20glossy%20%3Cem%3EMurder%20On%20The%20Orient%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2017)%20and%20star-filled%20%3Cem%3EDeath%20on%20The%20Nile%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2022).%20In%20Branagh%E2%80%99s%20third%20outing%20as%20Hercule%20Poirot%2C%20a%20sense%20of%20doom%20hangs%20over%20the%20film%20from%20the%20very%20first%20frame%20%E2%80%93%20a%20distinctly%20Hitchcockian%20visual%20of%20a%20murder%20of%20crows%20%E2%80%93%20after%20which%20a%20visibly%20traumatised%20Poirot%20wakes%20up%20in%20his%20apartment%20in%20Venice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20inspired%20choice%20that%20reveals%20Branagh%E2%80%99s%20plans%20to%20move%20away%20from%20glamour%20of%20his%20earlier%20films%20is%20the%20presence%20of%20composer%20Hildur%20Gu%C3%B0nad%C3%B3ttir%20%E2%80%93%20best%20known%20for%20%3Cem%3EJoker%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20%3Cem%3EChernobyl%3C%2Fem%3E%20(both%20released%20in%202019).%20Gu%C3%B0nad%C3%B3ttir%20%E2%80%93%20famous%20for%20her%20unconventional%20scores%20that%20convey%20mood%20rather%20than%20leaving%20the%20audience%20with%20%E2%80%98melodic%E2%80%99%20or%20%E2%80%98hummable%E2%80%99%20pieces%20%E2%80%93%20is%20an%20excellent%20choice%20to%20communicate%20the%20sense%20that%20something%E2%80%99s%20not%20quite%20right.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpening%20in%201947%20in%20the%20city%20of%20canals%2C%20we%E2%80%99re%20shown%20Poirot%20in%20self-imposed%20retirement.%20He%20has%20a%20bodyguard%20(Riccardo%20Scarmaccio)%20who%20ensures%20the%20detective%20can%20enjoy%20being%20retired%2C%20without%20being%20hounded%20by%20potential%20clients%20who%20queue%20up%20in%20front%20of%20his%20house%20every%20other%20day.%20He%E2%80%99s%20visited%20by%20a%20friend%20%E2%80%93%20a%20mystery%20writer%20called%20Ariadne%20Oliver%20(Tina%20Fey)%20%E2%80%93%20who%20as%20Poirot%20puts%20it%2C%20is%20there%20to%20seduce%20him%20with%20a%20case%20by%20provoking%20his%20curiosity.%20Oliver%20tells%20Poirot%20about%20a%20psychic%20named%20Joyce%20Reynolds%20(Michelle%20Yeoh)%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0%20only%20recently%20released%20from%20prison%20%E2%80%93%20claiming%20to%20be%20a%20medium%20who%20talks%20to%20people%20who%20have%20passed%20on.%20As%20a%20mystery%20writer%2C%20Oliver%20tells%20Poirot%20how%20she%E2%80%99s%20uncovered%20nearly%20all%20the%20fraudulent%20ways%20of%20Reynolds%E2%80%99%20kind%2C%20except%20for%20Reynolds%20herself.%20Oliver%20convinces%20Poirot%20to%20participate%20in%20a%20seance%20on%20Halloween%20night%20to%20uncover%20Reynolds%E2%80%99%20tricks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBased%20on%20Christie%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EHallowe%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%99%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3Een%20Party%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20fine%20set-up.%20What%20better%20way%20to%20start%20off%20a%20story%20about%20(probable)%20spirits%20and%20ghosts%20than%20to%20have%20one%20of%20the%20most%20staunch%20rationalists%20in%20the%20room%3F%20Branagh%20treats%20%3Cem%3EA%20Haunting%20in%20Venice%3C%2Fem%3E%20like%20a%20horror%20film.%20There%20are%20carefully%20crafted%20scares%20that%20are%20almost%20guaranteed%20to%20provoke%20a%20few%20screams%20in%20the%20theatre.%20Reynolds%E2%80%99%20character%20is%20introduced%20wearing%20a%20Noh%20mask%20%E2%80%93%20which%20goes%20on%20to%20become%20an%20important%20plot-point%20in%20the%20film.%20At%20one%20point%2C%20Poirot%20%E2%80%93%20whose%20disdain%20for%20the%20likes%20of%20Reynolds%20cannot%20be%20contained%20%E2%80%93%20is%20confronted%20by%20the%20psychic%20about%20knowing%20the%20curse%20of%20being%20the%20%E2%80%9Cgifted%E2%80%9D%20one.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20tremendous%20moment%20between%20towerings%20actors%20%E2%80%93%20Branagh%20and%20Yeoh%20%E2%80%93%20where%20the%20film%20hints%20that%20everything%20can%E2%80%99t%20have%20a%20reasonable%20explanation.%20It%E2%80%99s%20one%20of%20the%20finest%20attributes%20of%20the%20film%20%E2%80%93%20which%20merely%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20go%20about%20debunking%20the%20myths%20like%20a%20checklist%20%E2%80%93%20but%20also%20acknowledges%20that%20even%20the%20wisest%20among%20us%20can%E2%80%99t%20categorically%20explain%20every%20occurrence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20whodunit%20skeleton%20has%20gotten%20a%20reinvention%20over%20the%20past%20few%20years%2C%20most%20famously%20in%20Rian%20Johnson%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EKnives%20Out%3C%2Fem%3E%20films.%20Johnson%E2%80%99s%20films%20almost%20feel%20like%20feature-length%20winks%20at%20audiences%2C%20given%20how%20the%20films%20use%20the%20tropes%20of%20the%20genre%2C%20suffuse%20them%20with%20%E2%80%98topicality%E2%80%99%20and%20place%20dramatic%20actors%20(to%20varying%20degrees)%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20the%20most%20bizarre%20set-ups.%20And%20his%20films%20are%20undeniably%20sexy%20%E2%80%93%20with%20superb%20performances%2C%20and%20dazzling%20visual%20language%20%E2%80%93%20which%20could%20easily%20spawn%20replicas.%20Thankfully%2C%20Branagh%20goes%20in%20the%20opposite%20direction%20and%20treats%20his%20whodunit%20like%20a%20genre%20film%20rather%20than%20as%20a%20blockbuster.%20The%20result%20is%2C%20the%20visual%20language%20of%20a%20moody%20A24%20film%20(the%20studio%20behind%20the%20excellent%20%3Cem%3ETalk%20To%20Me%20%3C%2Fem%3Erecently)%2C%20rather%20than%20a%20standard%2020th%20Century%20production.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20gothic%20medieval%20architecture%2C%20Gu%C3%B0nad%C3%B3ttir%E2%80%99s%20foreboding%20score%2C%20Branagh%E2%80%99s%20most%20low-key%20ensemble%20%E2%80%93%20including%20Jamie%20Dornan%2C%20Kelly%20Reilly%2C%20Camille%20Cottin%2C%20Kyle%20Allen%2C%20apart%20from%20Fey%20and%20Yeoh%20%E2%80%93%20adds%20up%20to%20a%20mystery%20that%20ties%20up%20its%20loose%20ends%20neatly%2C%20perhaps%20too%20neatly%2C%20by%20the%20end%2C%20but%20one%20that%20also%20references%20old-school%20satisfaction%20of%20mysteries.%20Branagh%E2%80%99s%20ostentatious%20Belgian%20accent%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20get%20in%20the%20way%20of%20a%20haunted%20performance%20of%20a%20man%20%E2%80%93%20who%20knows%20everything%20there%20is%20to%20know%20%E2%80%93%20and%20yet%20seems%20to%20be%20grappling%20with%20the%20unknowables.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBranagh%E2%80%99s%20film%20even%20while%20flirting%20with%20the%20supernatural%20roots%20its%20horrors%20in%20the%20plausible.%20The%20palazzo%2C%20where%20a%20majority%20of%20the%20film%20unfolds%2C%20is%20said%20to%20have%20been%20an%20erstwhile%20children%E2%80%99s%20hospital%20%E2%80%93%20where%20doctors%20and%20nurses%20are%20believed%20to%20have%20locked%20and%20abandoned%20their%20patients%2C%20during%20the%20plague.%20A%20character%20recounts%20the%20terror%20he%20witnessed%20in%20the%20Second%20World%20War%20%E2%80%93%20leaving%20them%20with%20a%20permanent%20case%20of%20%E2%80%9CBattle%20Fever%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20making%20everyone%20jumpy%20during%20social%20gatherings%20and%20lash%20out%20during%20the%20most%20unexpected%20moments.%20Another%20character%20casually%20recounts%20how%20when%20they%20bumped%20into%20a%20battalion%20and%20mentally%20prepared%20to%20die%2C%20instead%20finding%20refuge%20in%20a%20Hollywood%20classic%20and%20watching%20it%20on%20repeat%20with%20friendly%20soldiers%20for%20a%20whole%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20boils%20down%20to%20a%20splendid%20thesis%20that%20even%2