0some%20point%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20not%20saying%20get%20out.%20I'm%20just%20saying%20that%20assets%20have%20to%20go%20up%20or%20else%20the%20economy%20will%20not%20do%20well.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJeffrey%20Gundlach%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimilarly%20titled%20the%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fbonds%2Fbill-gross-slams-jeff-gundlach-over-bond-king-nickname-2023-9%5C%22%3Ebond%20king%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20Gundlach%20expects%20a%20flood%20of%20Treasurys%2C%20warning%20that%20a%20coming%20recession%20will%20deepen%20the%20federal%20deficit.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20thing%20that%20will%20be%20so%20confounding%20to%20people%20is%20that%2C%20once%20we%20get%20deeper%20into%20the%20recession%2C%20bond%20yields%20will%20actually%20start%20to%20go%20up%20because%20of%20excessive%20money%20printing%20and%20monetary%20response%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjeffrey-gundlach-doubleline-us-economic-outlook-recession-inflation-debt-spending-2023-9%5C%22%3EFox%20Business%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20many%20economists%20have%20warmed%20to%20the%20prospect%20of%20a%20soft%20landing%2C%20Gundlach%20maintains%20that%20a%20recession%20is%20likely%20in%20six%20to%20eight%20months%2C%20as%20pandemic-era%20consumer%20savings%20are%20depleted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20this%20happens%20amid%20the%20Fed's%20tight%20policy%2C%20the%20economy%20could%20spiral%20into%20deflation%2C%20he%20predicted%2C%20forcing%20the%20government%20to%20go%20deeper%20into%20debt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20the%20Fed%2C%20in%20the%20back%20of%20their%20mind%2C%20realizes%20that%20when%20the%20next%20recession%20comes%2C%20the%20amount%20of%20borrowing%20is%20going%20to%20be%20so%20enormous%20that%20it's%20going%20to%20be%20a%20really%20bad%20idea%20to%20have%20interest%20rates%20higher%20than%205%25%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp