t%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edidn't%20contain%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmanhattan-project-scientists-killed-demon-core-2023-7%5C%22%3Eplutonium%20capsule%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20Richardson%20jettisoned%20it.%20A%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FAtomicAnalyst%2Fstatus%2F1622250953847050242%2Fphoto%2F2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereceipt%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20bomb%20that%20Richardson%20signed%20at%20the%20time%20said%20he%20wouldn't%20allow%20the%20insertion%20of%20an%20%26quot%3Bactive%20capsule%26quot%3B%20into%20the%20weapon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FAtomicAnalyst%2Fstatus%2F1622251183539634177%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E1966%20letter%3C%2Fa%3E%20declassified%20in%201994%20complicated%20the%20picture.%20It%20referred%20to%20then-Assistant%20Defense%20Secretary%20Jack%20Howard's%20testimony%20before%20a%20congressional%20committee%20calling%20the%20Tybee%20bomb%20a%20complete%20nuclear%20weapon%2C%20with%20plutonium%20included.%20In%202001%2C%20a%20military%20spokesman%20told%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theatlantic.com%2Fmagazine%2Farchive%2F2001%2F07%2Fthe-colonel-and-the-bomb%2F302260%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Atlantic%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20they%20had%20recently%20spoken%20with%20Howard%2C%20and%20%26quot%3Bhe%20agreed%20that%20his%20memo%20was%20in%20error.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20know%20some%20people%20think%20it's%20settled%2C%26quot%3B%20Schwartz%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20haven't%20fully%20made%20up%20my%20mind%2C%20but%20I%20feel%20like%20I%20am%20more%20comfortable%20going%20with%20the%20contemporaneous%20accounts.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EDetecting%20a%20bomb%20underwater%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202000%2C%20retired%20Air%20Force%20officer%20Derek%20Duke%20contacted%20then-Rep.%20Jack%20Kingston%20of%20Georgia%20about%20the%20missing%20bomb%20and%20Howard's%20memo%2C%20CBS%20News%20reported.%20At%20the%20congressman's%20urging%2C%20the%20Air%20Force%20looked%20into%20the%20pros%20and%20cons%20of%20trying%20to%20locate%20and%20remove%20the%20weapon%20versus%20leaving%20it%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%202001%20report%20suggested%20recovery%20cost%20would%20start%20at%20%245%20million%2C%20and%20that%20there%20was%20%26quot%3Ba%20very%20low%20possibility%20of%20successfully%20locating%20the%20bomb.%26quot%3B%20There%20was%20little%20chance%20it%20would%20spontaneously%20explode%2C%20it%20didn't%20contain%20plutonium%2C%20and%20the%20biggest%20environmental%20risk%20was%20heavy%20metal%20contamination%20as%20the%20bomb%20corroded%2C%20the%20report%20concluded.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20there%20was%20a%20chance%20of%20it%20exploding%20during%20retrieval%2C%20and%20experts%20would%20have%20to%20remove%20and%20dispose%20of%20the%20uranium%20first.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221999%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20yellow%20boat%20with%20several%20people%20aboard%20off%20the%20coast%20of%20Little%20Tybee%2C%20Georgia%20looking%20for%20a%20missing%20nuclear%20weapon%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65034021992da60019ec8cde%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221499%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20boat%20searches%20the%20waters%20of%20Wassaw%20Sound%20for%20the%20nuclear%20weapon%20that%20a%20B-47%20dropped%20decades%20earlier.%3Cp%3EGerald%20Weaver%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20whole%20Air%20Force%20perspective%20is%2C%20it's%20just%20not%20worth%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Schwartz%20said.%20%26quot%3BTrying%20to%20move%20it%20could%20create%20bigger%20problems%20than%20if%20we%20just%20leave%20it%20where%20it%20is.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%202001%20Air%20Force%20report%20estimated%20the%207%2C600-pound%20lost%20bomb%20had%20400%20pounds%20of%20conventional%20explosive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENevertheless%2C%20Duke%20took%20it%20upon%20himself%20to%20find%20the%20weapon.%20In%202004%2C%20he%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fabcnews.go.com%2FTechnology%2Fstory%3Fid%3D99459%26page%3D1%5C%22%3Ethought%20he%20had%20it%3C%2Fa%3E.%20His%20equipment%20picked%20up%20unusually%20high%20radiation%20readings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Air%20Force%20investigated%20but%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.proquest.com%2Fdocview%2F389907666%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20radiation%20was%20from%20naturally%20occurring%20minerals%20in%20Wassaw%20Sound.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20a%20decade%20later%2C%20in%202015%2C%20another%20citizen%20found%20strange%20sonar%20readings.%20The%20Nuclear%20Emergency%20Support%20Team%20advised%20on%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebulletin.org%2Fpremium%2F2023-03%2Fnerds-ninjas-and-neutrons-the-story-of-the-nuclear-emergency-support-team%2F%23post-heading%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOperation%20Sleeping%20Dog%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20when%20military%20divers%20again%20searched%20for%20and%20failed%20to%20find%20the%20nearly%2012-foot-long%20bomb.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Department%20of%20Energy%20sent%20subject%20matter%20experts%20to%20examine%20what%20the%20citizen%20searchers%20found%20in%202015%2C%20Shayela%20Hassan%2C%20deputy%20director%20of%20the%20Office%20of%20Communications%20with%20the%20National%20Nuclear%20Security%20Administration%2C%20said%20in%20an%20emailed%20statement%20to%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDOE's%20assessment%20of%20the%20material%20presented%20in%202015%20was%20that%20the%20search%20lacked%20any%20evidence%20that%20supported%20discovery%20of%20the%20lost%20weapon%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20statement%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20agency%20statement%20continued%3A%20%26quot%3BPeriodic%20announcements%20by%20private%20citizens%20that%20the%20bomb%20may%20have%20been%20located%20have%20prompted%20mobilizations%20of%20US%20Government%20personnel%2C%20diverting%20them%20from%20more%20pressing%20national%20security%20and%20public%20health%20responsibilities.%20As%20such%2C%20DOE%20does%20not%20encourage%20private%20searches%20for%20the%20device.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchwartz%20thinks%20the%20only%20way%20the%20weapon%20will%20be%20found%20is%20by%20chance%20or%20if%20a%20powerful%20storm%20dredges%20it%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20won't%20say%20it's%20lost%20for%20the%20ages%20because%20I%20don't%20think%20it%20is%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20but%20%26quot%3Bso%20many%20people%20have%20searched%20for%20it%20for%20so%20long%20using%20some%20fairly%20sophisticated%20equipment%20and%20not%20found%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EOne%20mishap%20among%20many%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELess%20than%20a%20month%20after%20Richardson%20jettisoned%20the%20Tybee%20bomb%2C%20another%20B-47%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.atlasobscura.com%2Fplaces%2Fmars-bluff-crater%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccidentally%20dropped%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20nuclear%20weapon%20on%20South%20Carolina.%20It%20didn't%20contain%20plutonium%20but%20left%20a%2050-foot%20crater%20in%20a%20family's%20yard.%20A%20few%20family%20members%20had%20minor%20injuries%20but%20everyone%20survived.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%201950%2C%20the%20US%20military%20has%20been%20involved%20in%2032%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.atomicarchive.com%2Falmanac%2Fbroken-arrows%2Findex.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebroken%20arrow%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20incidents%2C%20where%20they%20lost%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnuclear-bomb-accident-goldsboro-nc-swamp-2017-5%5C%22%3Edropped%20nuclear%20weapons%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20other%20issues%2C%20like%20fires%2C%20were%20involved.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221999%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Several%20people%20stand%20around%20a%20large%20crater%20on%20a%20family%20farm%20in%20South%20Carolina%20after%20a%20B-47%20accidentally%20dropped%20a%20bomb%20in%20the%201950s%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65048026956dba001ace825d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221499%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESeveral%20people%20inspect%20the%20deep%20crater%20made%20when%20a%20B-47%20accidentally%20dropped%20a%20nuclear%20weapon%20in%201958.%3Cp%3EBettmann%2FContributor%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20book%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.penguinrandomhouse.com%2Fbooks%2F303337%2Fcommand-and-control-by-eric-schlosser%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECommand%20and%20Control%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20Eric%20Schlosser%20wrote%20that%20in%201957%20Air%20Force%20planes%20unintentionally%20dropped%20a%20nuclear%20weapon%20once%20every%20320%20flights.%20Coupled%20with%20the%20high%20rate%20of%20B-52%20bomber%20crashes%2C%20there%20was%20the%20potential%20for%20about%2019%20incidents%20involving%20nuclear%20weapons%20each%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBetween%201960%20and%201968%2C%20the%20US%20military%20kept%20jets%20armed%20with%20nuclear%20weapons%20at%20the%20ready%20in%20case%20of%20a%20surprise%20nuclear%20attack.%20A%20series%20of%20near%20misses%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-air-force-lost-nuclear-bombs-in-spain-2018-1%5C%22%3Eserious%20accidents%20with%20nuclear%20weapons%3C%2Fa%3E%20caused%20the%20Air%20Force%20to%20end%20the%20program.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20think%20we're%20going%20to%20go%20back%20to%20the%20bad%20old%20days%20of%20putting%20our%20nuclear%20weapons%20on%20aircraft%2C%26quot%3B%20Schwartz%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E(In%202007%2C%20a%20B-52%20bomber%20was%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.airforcetimes.com%2Fnews%2Fyour-air-force%2F2019%2F06%2F25%2Fyou-can-call-2007-nuke-mishandling-an-embarrassment-but-