self-expression%20and%20state%20control.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20has%20been%20several%20weeks%20since%20Boris%20Kagarlitsky%2C%20a%20prominent%20figure%20in%20the%20Russian%20Leftist%20intellectual%20sphere%2C%20a%20distinguished%20social%20scientist%20and%20prolific%20political%20writer%2C%20was%20arrested.%20On%20July%2025%2C%20an%20unexpected%20turn%20of%20events%20unfolded%20for%20Kagarlitsky%20as%20he%20was%20hurriedly%20arrested%20and%20transported%20over%201000%20kilometres%20away%20from%20Moscow%20to%20Syktyvkar%20in%20the%20Komi%20Republic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20same%20day%2C%20a%20local%20court%20ruled%20to%20detain%20him%20for%20a%20duration%20of%20two%20months%2C%20all%20emerging%20from%20allegations%20related%20to%20his%20purported%20support%20for%20%E2%80%98acts%20of%20terrorism%E2%80%99.%20The%20potential%20consequences%20of%20this%20situation%20loom%20large%2C%20as%20a%20guilty%20verdict%20from%20the%20court%20could%20subject%20Kagarlitsky%20to%20the%20grim%20possibility%20of%20a%20prison%20sentence%20extending%20up%20to%20seven%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EUnwavering%20commitment%20to%20activism%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Kagarlitsky%20this%20was%20not%20the%20first%20episode%20of%20incarceration.%20Way%20back%20in%201982%2C%20he%20confronted%20a%20hard%20time%20when%20he%20was%20jailed%20due%20to%20his%20association%20with%20a%20group%20of%20%E2%80%98Young%20Socialists%E2%80%99%20who%20openly%20criticised%20the%20Soviet%20bureaucratic%20leadership.%20Notwithstanding%20this%20setback%2C%20Kagarlitsky%20remained%20deeply%20involved%20in%20the%20political%20sphere%2C%20particularly%20during%20Gorbachev%E2%80%99s%20Perestroika%20era.%20Throughout%20these%20years%2C%20he%20undertook%20a%20parallel%20journey%2C%20producing%20intellectually%20stimulating%20works%20that%20delved%20into%20intricate%20social%20and%20political%20matters.%20Over%20the%20subsequent%20three%20and%20a%20half%20decades%2C%20his%20literary%20output%20thrived%2C%20resulting%20in%20a%20multitude%20of%20influential%20books%20and%20essays%20that%20have%20made%20significant%20contributions%20to%20the%20discourse%20on%20these%20critical%20subjects.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKagarlitsky%20served%20as%20a%20professor%20at%20the%20Moscow%20School%20for%20Social%20and%20Economic%20Sciences%20and%20the%20editor%20of%20the%20influential%20left-wing%20media%20outlet%20%3Cem%3ERabkor%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Kagarlitsky%E2%80%99s%20academic%20journey%20began%20with%20a%20focus%20on%20theatre%20criticism%2C%20but%20his%20involvement%20in%20dissident%20activities%20led%20to%20his%20expulsion%20in%201980.%20He%20served%20as%20the%20editor%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98samizdat%20journal%20Levy%20Povorot%E2%80%99%20and%20was%20arrested%20on%20%E2%80%98anti-Soviet%E2%80%99%20charges%2C%20eventually%20released%20in%201983.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20Mikhail%20Gorbachev%E2%80%99s%20perestroika%2C%20Kagarlitsky%20resumed%20his%20studies%20and%20became%20involved%20in%20political%20activism.%20He%20played%20a%20key%20role%20in%20various%20political%20organisations%2C%20including%20the%20Moscow%20People%E2%80%99s%20Front%2C%20Moscow%20City%20Soviet%2C%20and%20the%20Socialist%20Party%20(USSR)%2C%20and%20co-founded%20the%20Party%20of%20Labour%20(Russia)%20in%201992.%20In%201993%2C%20Kagarlitsky%20was%20again%20arrested%20for%20opposing%20President%20Boris%20Yeltsin%20during%20the%20constitutional%20crisis%20but%20was%20released%20due%20to%20international%20protests.%20His%20job%20and%20the%20Moscow%20City%20Soviet%20were%20dissolved%20later%20that%20year%20under%20Yeltsin%E2%80%99s%20new%20constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%201994%20to%202002%2C%20he%20worked%20as%20a%20senior%20research%20fellow%20at%20the%20Institute%20for%20Comparative%20Political%20Studies%20of%20the%20Russian%20Academy%20of%20Sciences%20and%20earned%20his%20Doctorate%20degree%20in%201995%20for%20his%20thesis%20on%20%E2%80%9CCollective%20Actions%20and%20Labour%20Policies%20in%20Russia%20in%20the%2090s%E2%80%9D.%20He%20has%20also%20been%20associating%20with%20the%20Institute%20of%20Globalisation%20Studies%20and%20Social%20Movements%2C%20Transnational%20Institute%2C%20etc.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarlier%2C%20Kagarlitsky%E2%80%99s%20book%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.versobooks.com%2Fen-gb%2Fproducts%2F1242-the-thinking-reed%5C%22%3EThinking%20Reed%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%20earned%20him%20the%20prestigious%20Isaac%20Deutscher%20Prize.%20He%20expanded%20his%20influence%20internationally%20with%20works%20like%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.versobooks.com%2Fproducts%2F1288-the-dialectic-of-change%5C%22%3EDialectics%20of%20Change%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.versobooks.com%2Fproducts%2F1301-farewell-perestroika%5C%22%3EA%20Farewell%20To%20Perestroika%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20initially%20in%20English%20and%20later%20translated%20into%20Japanese%20and%20Turkish.%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.abebooks.com%2Fbook-search%2Fisbn%2F9780853458920%2F%5C%22%3ESquare%20Wheels%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20among%20many%20other%20works%2C%20also%20received%20a%20wide%20readership.%20He%20later%20took%20charge%20as%20a%20professor%20at%20the%20Moscow%20School%20for%20the%20Social%20and%20Economic%20Sciences%2C%20enriching%20academia%20with%20his%20insights.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20late%2C%20Kagarlitsky%E2%80%99s%20unwavering%20commitment%20to%20activism%20has%20taken%20a%20toll%20on%20his%20personal%20life%2C%20exemplified%20by%20his%20ill-timed%20arrests%20and%20repeated%20legal%20penalties.%20His%20unyielding%20dedication%20to%20democratic%20principles%20has%20driven%20him%20to%20take%20bold%20actions.%20In%202020%2C%20he%20organised%20a%20rally%20to%20oppose%20constitutional%20changes%20that%20could%20potentially%20enable%20President%20Putin%20to%20seek%20a%20fifth%20term%20in%20office.%20Similarly%2C%20in%202021%2C%20he%20used%20social%20media%20to%20mobilise%20support%20for%20protests%20against%20alleged%20voter%20fraud.%20These%20principled%20actions%20drew%20the%20attention%20of%20authorities%2C%20resulting%20in%20legal%20repercussions%20for%20Kagarlitsky.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F28154812%2FVlad.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F28154812%2FVlad.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F28154812%2FVlad-300x150.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F28154812%2FVlad-1024x513.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F28154812%2FVlad-800x400.jpg%20800w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-660575%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22601%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EVladimir%20Putin.%20Photo%3A%20Wikimedia%20Commons%2Fwww.kremlin.ru.%20CC%20BY-SA%204.0.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20Kagarlitsky%20faced%20yet%20another%20daunting%20hurdle%20as%20he%20was%20officially%20labelled%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.marxist.com%2Frussia-who-is-boris-kagarlitsky-and-why-is-he-being-prosecuted.htm%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98foreign%20agent%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fa%3E%20This%20designation%2C%20carrying%20significant%20legal%20implications%2C%20complicated%20his%20ability%20to%20freely%20express%20his%20views.%20It%20was%20a%20consequence%20of%20his%20steadfast%20internationalist%20stance%20on%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20war%20on%20Ukraine%2C%20a%20position%20that%20had%20drawn%20the%20ire%20of%20the%20authorities.%20Remarkably%2C%20despite%20the%20increasing%20adversities%2C%20Kagarlitsky%20demonstrated%20steadfast%20resilience.%20He%20chose%20not%20to%20leave%20the%20country%2C%20and%20even%20more%20notably%2C%20he%20refused%20to%20retreat%20from%20the%20public%20arena.%20His%20determination%20to%20persist%20in%20his%20work%20and%20advocacy%20in%20the%20face%20of%20such%20challenges%20serve%20as%20powerful%20evidence%20of%20his%20resolute%20commitment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fukraines-protracted-struggle-for-national-liberation%5C%22%3EUkraine%E2%80%99s%20Protracted%20Struggle%20for%20National%20Liberation%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKagarlitsky%E2%80%99s%20writings%20have%20played%20a%20pivotal%20role%20in%20shaping%20the%20intellectual%20development%20of%20successive%20generations%20of%20young%20Russian%20communists%20and%20adherents%20of%20Leftist%20ideologies.%20His%20scholarly%20contributions%20stand%20as%20a%20potent%20counterbalance%20to%20the%20enduring%20influence%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.marxist.com%2Frussia-who-is-boris-kagarlitsky-and-why-is-he-being-prosecuted.htm%5C%22%3Elate-Soviet%2C%20Stalinist%20%E2%80%98official%20Marxism%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%C2%A0Yet%2C%20Kagarlitsky%E2%80%99s%20dedication%20to%20his%20cause%20transcends%20the%20realm%20of%20writing.%20He%20consistently%20extended%20intellectual%20support%20to%20fellow%20left-wing%20activists%2C%20offering%20his%20expertise%20whenever%20the%20occasion%20demanded.%20His%20commitment%20exceeded%20the%20boundaries%20of%20academic%20pursuits%2C%20as%20he%20rarely%20declined%20opportunities%20to%20engage%20in%20intellectual%20discourse%20with%20matching%20essences%20at%20various%20left-wing%20conferences%20and%20gatherings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20March%2021%2C%202023%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcanadiandimension.com%2Farticles%2Fview%2Fthe-tragedy-of-war%5C%22%3EKagarlitsky%20wrote%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20Ukraine%20war%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CFor%20many%20years%2C%20I%E2%80%99ve%20criticised%20Western%20policies%20towards%20Ukraine%20and%20media%20myths%20about%20it.%20But%20today%2C%20both%20Ukraine%20and%20Russia%20face%20new%20and%20complex%20challenges.%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20regime%20has%20shifted%20from%20moderate%20authoritarianism%20to%20a%20more%20totalitarian%20system.%20It%E2%80%99s%20crucial%20not%20to%20conflate%20Ukrainian%20politics%20with%20the%20ongoing%20war%E2%80%A6Ukraine%20has%20its%20issues%2C%20including%20controversial%20language%20legislation%20and%20problematic%20policies%20towards%20Donbas.%20Human%20rights%20violations%20have%20occurred%20on%20both%20sides%20since%20the%202014%20conflict.%20However%2C%20these%20issues%20can%E2%80%99t%20justify%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20massive%20invasion%20of%20Ukrainian%20territory.%20Efforts%20to%20rationalize%20the%20Kremlin%E2%80%99s%20decision%20as%20defending%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20interests%20lack%20credibility%20and%20don%E2%80%99t%20hold%20up%20to%20scrutiny.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcanadiandimension.com%2Farticles%2Fview%2Fthe-tragedy-of-war%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20Kagarlitsky%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CUkraine%20is%20now%20a%20victim%20of%20aggression.%20And%20no%20matter%20what%20we%20may%20think%20of%20the%20Kyiv%20government%2C%20any%20attempt%20to%20deny%20it%20amounts%20to%20nothing%20but%20plain%20victim%20blaming.%20Poland%20in%201939%20was%20not%20a%20nice%20place%20either%20and%20it%20really%20did%20discriminate%20against%20its%20ethnic%20minorities%2C%20including%20Germans%2C%20but%20this%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20justify%20or%20even%20explain%20Hitler%E2%80%99s%20invasion.%20Donbas%20was%20nothing%20but%20a%20pretext%3B%20most%20of%20the%20motives%20for%20the%20war%20in%202022%20were%20purely%20domestic.%20It%20was%20an%20attempt%20to%20restore%20the%20shattered%20support%20for%20the%20regime%20in%20the%20face%20of%20mounting%20social%20and%20economic%20crisis.%20Growing%20popular%20discontent%20in%20Russia%20forced%20the%20regime%20to%20resort%20to%20massive%20electoral%20fraud%20in%202020%20and%202021%20and%20to%20step%20up%20repression.%20One%20anti-democratic%20law%20after%20another%20was%20passed%2C%20thousands%20of%20people%20were%20imprisoned%20and%20many%20were%20forced%20to%20leave%20the%20country.%20Universities%20were%20purged%20of%20liberal%20and%20leftist%20teachers%2C%20independent%20print%20media%20was%20shut%20down%20and%20attempts%20were%20made%20to%20impose%20Internet%20censorship.%20Critics%20of%20the%20regime%20were%20officially%20labelled%20%E2%80%9Cforeign%20agents%E2%80%9D%20and%20deprived%20of%20political%20rights.%20This%20all%20happened%20even%20before%20the%20eruption%20of%20the%20war%20which%20was%20only%20used%20post-factum%20to%20justify%20and%20intensify%20these%20measures.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcanadiandimension.com%2Farticles%2Fview%2Fthe-tragedy-of-war%5C%22%3EKagarlitsky%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20regime%E2%80%99s%20support%20continued%20to%20dwindle%20due%20to%20its%20own%20incompetence%20and%20the%20global%20crisis%20of%20neoliberalism%20affecting%20Russia%20and%20many%20other%20nations.%20The%20ruling%20elite%20desperately%20sought%20a%20remedy%20to%20reestablish%20societal%20cohesion.%20Moreover%2C%20concerns%20over%20the%20aging%20dictator%E2%80%99s%20health%20prompted%20discussions%20about%20a%20transition%20plan%20to%20maintain%20control%20over%20the%20political%20landscape.%20The%20idea%20of%20a%20%E2%80%98short%20victorious%20war%E2%80%99%20appeared%20as%20a%20panacea%20to%20address%20these%20issues%20simultaneously.%20However%2C%20their%20calculations%20went%20awry.%20The%20blitzkrieg%20strategy%20faltered%2C%20and%20instead%20of%20a%20triumphant%20advance%20to%20Kyiv%2C%20they%20found%20themselves%20embroiled%20in%20a%20protracted%2C%20unwinnable%20war.%20He%20said%20that%20the%20war%20had%20fuelled%20radical%20nationalism%2C%20now%20the%20Kremlin%E2%80%99s%20dominant%20ideology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F02%2F20165942%2F51905521463_0600c20141_k.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F02%2F20165942%2F51905521463_0600c20141_k.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F02%2F20165942%2F51905521463_0600c20141_k-300x200.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F02%2F20165942%2F51905521463_0600c20141_k-1024x683.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-641263%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20protest%20against%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine.%20Photo%3A%20pix-4-2-day%2FFlickr%20CC%20BY%20NC%20ND%202.0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EPutin%E2%80%99s%20circle%20and%20propaganda%20openly%20advocate%20for%20the%20elimination%20of%20Ukraine%2C%20politically%20and%20physically.%20This%20poses%20a%20growing%20threat%2C%20not%20just%20to%20Ukraine%2C%20which%20defends%20itself%20with%20Western%20support%2C%20but%20to%20Russian%20society%20itself.%20Defeating%20the%20Russian%20army%20is%20the%20only%20solution%20to%20counter%20the%20encroachment%20of%20reactionary%20forces%20destroying%20education%20and%20human%20rights%20in%20Russia.%20Putin%E2%80%99s%20victory%20would%20be%20catastrophic%20for%20modern%20Russia.%20Fortunately%2C%20his%20army%20is%20facing%20defeat%2C%20opening%20the%20door%20to%20revolutionary%20change%2C%20he%20said.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcanadiandimension.com%2Farticles%2Fview%2Fthe-tragedy-of-war%5C%22%3EKagarlitsky%20further%20noted%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20what%20troubles%20him%20about%20Western%20liberal%20pacifism%20was%20its%20failure%20to%20acknowledge%20the%20diverse%20interests%2C%20opinions%2C%20and%20rights%20of%20Ukrainians%2C%20Russians%2C%20Crimeans%2C%20and%20Donbas%20residents.%20The%20suffering%20of%20civilians%20resulted%20from%20concrete%20aggression%20by%20Putin%E2%80%99s%20forces%2C%20and%20it%E2%80%99s%20crucial%20to%20recognize%20and%20respect%20these%20people%E2%80%99s%20interests.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20an%20interview%20with%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.democracynow.org%2F2022%2F12%2F8%2Frussia_ukraine_war_fatigue_boris_kagarlitsky%5C%22%3EDemocracy%20Now%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%20on%20December%208%2C%202022%2C%20Boris%20was%20asked%20by%20Amy%20Goodman%20if%20he%20had%20concerns%20about%20his%20personal%20safety%20while%20speaking%20in%20Moscow.%20Boris%20responded%2C%20%E2%80%9CNot%20more%20than%20anybody%20else%20in%20Russia%20these%20days.%E2%80%9D%20He%20said%20the%20government%20declared%20him%20a%20%E2%80%98foreign%20agent%2C%E2%80%99%20though%20they%20failed%20to%20specify%20which%20country%20he%20was%20an%20agent%20for.%20Boris%20said%20he%20didn%E2%80%99t%20believe%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20need%20to%20be%20overly%20fearful.%20He%20had%20experienced%20imprisonment%20in%20Russia%20on%20at%20least%20two%20occasions%2C%20and%20he%20has%20been%20here%20for%20many%20years%2C%20witnessing%20various%20changes%20in%20regimes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlex%20Callinicos%2C%20an%20internationally%20reputed%20left%20political%20theorist%2C%20wrote%20in%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsocialistworker.co.uk%2Falex-callinicos%2Fback-jailed-russian-socialist-boris-kagarlitsky%2F%5C%22%3ESocialist%20Worker%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3A%20Boris%20stands%20as%20a%20living%20embodiment%20of%20this%20unique%20group%20%E2%80%93%20possessing%20erudition%2C%20fluency%20in%20multiple%20languages%2C%20and%20an%20abundance%20of%20humour%20and%20charm.%20Yet%2C%20beneath%20these%20qualities%20lies%20a%20profound%20commitment%20to%20anti-capitalist%20and%20anti-imperialist%20ideals.%20Callinicos%20said%20that%20throughout%20their%20shared%20history%2C%20their%20political%20strategies%20have%20seldom%20aligned.%20Boris%E2%80%99s%20unwavering%20adherence%20to%20the%20principles%20of%20the%20early%2020th-century%20French%20socialist%2C%20Jean%20Jaur%C3%A8s%2C%20has%20been%20a%20defining%20feature%20of%20his%20approach.%20Jaur%C3%A8s%20contended%20that%20%E2%80%9Creform%20and%20revolution%2C%20far%20from%20being%20mutually%20exclusive%2C%20augment%20and%20are%20conditioned%20by%20one%20another%2C%E2%80%9D%20a%20philosophy%20Boris%20has%20faithfully%20embraced.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20noted%20that%20in%20practical%20terms%2C%20this%20translates%20into%20a%20form%20of%20radical%20reformism%2C%20wherein%20Boris%20seeks%20%E2%80%9Crevolutionary%E2%80%9D%20or%20%E2%80%9Cirreversible%E2%80%9D%20reforms%20capable%20of%20reshaping%20the%20very%20foundations%20of%20capitalism.%20Regrettably%2C%20the%20neoliberal%20era%20has%20demonstrated%20that%20no%20reform%20is%20truly%20irreversible.%20Nevertheless%2C%20Boris%20remains%20steadfast%20in%20his%20determination%20to%20resist%20what%20he%20terms%20the%20%E2%80%9Cnew%20barbarism%E2%80%9D%20inherent%20in%20contemporary%20capitalism%2C%20a%20commitment%20that%20has%20consistently%20placed%20him%20at%20the%20forefront%20of%20global%20protest%20movements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECallinicos%20also%20critically%20viewed%20his%20position%3A%20%E2%80%9CBoris%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20always%20made%20the%20right%20political%20calls.%20The%20brutality%20and%20corruption%20of%20the%20Russian%20version%20of%20neoliberalism%20has%20tempted%20him%20sometimes%20to%20ally%20with%20ideologically%20reactionary%20forces%20opposed%20to%20Western%20imperialism%20and%20its%20allies%20in%20central%20and%20eastern%20Europe.%20Thus%20in%202014%2C%20he%20made%20the%20mistake%20of%20welcoming%20the%20pro-Russian%20separatist%20revolts%20in%20eastern%20Ukraine%20as%20%E2%80%98a%20revolutionary%20movement%E2%80%99.%20However%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsocialistworker.co.uk%2Falex-callinicos%2Fback-jailed-russian-socialist-boris-kagarlitsky%2F%5C%22%3ECallinicos%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CBoris%20has%20been%20a%20staunch%20opponent%20of%20the%20Russian%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20in%20February%202022.%20He%20argues%20that%20%E2%80%98most%20of%20the%20motives%20for%20the%20war%20in%202022%20were%20purely%20domestic.%20It%20was%20an%20attempt%20to%20restore%20the%20shattered%20support%20for%20the%20regime%20in%20the%20face%20of%20mounting%20social%20and%20economic%20crisis.%E2%80%99%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKagarlitsky%E2%80%99s%20approachability%20and%20openness%20enriched%20left-wing%20gatherings%20by%20fostering%20dynamic%20discussions.%20His%20impact%20extends%20well%20beyond%20his%20writings.%20Since%202008%2C%20he%E2%80%99s%20played%20a%20vital%20role%20as%20a%20founder%20and%20editor%20of%20Rabkor%2C%20a%20prominent%20online%20journal%20and%20YouTube%20channel%20for%20left-wing%20discourse.%20His%20essays%20and%20columns%20on%20Rabkor%20have%20attracted%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20readers%2C%20establishing%20him%20as%20a%20respected%20figure%20in%20the%20Russian%20left.%20His%20insightful%20analyses%20have%20shaped%20left-wing%20discourse%2C%20solidifying%20his%20influence%20on%20political%20and%20social%20discussions%20in%20Russia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECritics%20argue%20that%20Boris%20Kagarlitsky%E2%80%99s%20charges%20emerged%20solely%20from%20one%20of%20his%20Telegram%20posts%2C%20in%20which%20he%20analysed%20the%20Ukrainian%20attack%20on%20the%20Crimean%20Bridge%20on%20October%208%2C%202022.%20It%E2%80%99s%20evident%20that%20there%20is%20no%20endorsement%20of%20terrorism%20in%20this%20post.%20This%20incident%20highlights%20how%20law%20enforcement%20often%20employs%20weak%20pretexts%20for%20charges.%20In%20response%20to%20Kagarlitsky%E2%80%99s%20arrest%2C%20a%20coalition%2C%20primarily%20comprising%20left-wing%20groups%2C%20has%20launched%20a%20vigorous%20public%20campaign%20for%20his%20release%20and%20justice.%20This%20multifaceted%20campaign%20includes%20publishing%20numerous%20articles%2C%20distributing%20informative%20leaflets%2C%20and%20organizing%20public%20meetings.%20These%20efforts%20aim%20not%20only%20to%20raise%20awareness%20but%20also%20have%20the%20potential%20to%20unite%20diverse%20groups%20with%20a%20shared%20cause.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20plea%20for%20help%20from%20people%20worldwide%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.versobooks.com%2Fen-gb%2Fblogs%2Fnews%2Fsolidarity-needed-for-russian-anti-war-socialist-boris-kagarlitsky%5C%22%3Ethe%20%3Cem%3ERabkor%3C%2Fem%3E%20editorial%20board%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20%E2%80%9CBoris%20is%20not%20just%20a%20famous%20left-wing%20thinker%20and%20scholar%3B%20he%E2%80%99s%20also%20a%20Marxist%20who%20has%20studied%20class%20conflicts%2C%20was%20a%20Soviet%20left-wing%20dissident%2C%20and%20now%20might%20end%20up%20as%20a%20political%20prisoner%20in%20Putin%E2%80%99s%20Russia.%20He%E2%80%99s%20part%20of%20the%20global%20socialist%20movement%2C%20has%20taught%20many%20Marxists%2C%20and%20has%20stayed%20true%20to%20his%20beliefs%20for%20a%20long%20time.%20Kagarlitsky%20shouldn%E2%80%99t%20be%20in%20jail%20because%2C%20in%202023%2C%20politics%20shouldn%E2%80%99t%20be%20seen%20as%20a%20crime.%20We%20strongly%20disagree%20with%20his%20arrest.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20August%2016%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fznetwork.org%2Fznetarticle%2Fkagarlitsky-letter-from-prison%2F%5C%22%3EKagarlitsky%20wrote%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20prison%3A%20%E2%80%9CI%20think%20that%20the%20current%20arrest%20can%20be%20considered%20a%20recognition%20of%20the%20political%20significance%20of%20my%20statements.%20Of%20course%2C%20I%20would%20have%20preferred%20to%20be%20recognised%20in%20a%20somewhat%20different%20form%2C%20but%20all%20in%20good%20time.%20In%20the%2040-odd%20years%20since%20my%20first%20arrest%2C%20I%20have%20learned%20to%20be%20patient%20and%20to%20realize%20how%20fickle%20political%20fortune%20in%20Russia%20is.%20The%20experience%20of%20the%20past%20years%2C%20it%20would%20seem%2C%20does%20not%20dispose%20much%20to%20optimism.%20But%20historical%20experience%20as%20a%20whole%20is%20much%20richer%20and%20gives%20much%20more%20grounds%20for%20positive%20expectations.%20Remember%20what%20Shakespeare%20wrote%20in%20Macbeth%3F%20%E2%80%9CThe%20night%20is%20long%20that%20never%20finds%20the%20day.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20global%20movement%20is%20actively%20working%20towards%20securing%20Kagarlitsky%E2%80%99s%20freedom.%20The%20ongoing%20efforts%20include%20the%20organisation%20of%20gatherings%20and%20protests%20calling%20for%20his%20release%20and%20justice.%20These%20events%20are%20planned%20to%20take%20place%20in%20different%20cities%20around%20the%20world%20on%20September%2016.%20%3Cem%3E%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EK.M.%20Seethi%20is%20a%20Senior%20Fellow%20at%20the%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3EIndian%20Council%20of%20Social%20Science%20Research%20(ICSSR).%20He%20is%20also%20the%20Director%20of%20the%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3EInter-University%20Centre%20for%20Social%20Science%20Research%20and%20Extension%20(IUCSSRE)%2C%20Mahatma%20Gandhi%20University%2C%20Kerala.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694851391000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F16131315%2FThe-Wire-12.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Ffreedom-for-boris-kagarlitsky-activists-globally-extend-support-to-jailed-russian-intellectual%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20prominent%20figure%20in%20the%20Russian%20Leftist%20intellectual%20sphere%2C%20a%20distinguished%20social%20scientist%20and%20prolific%20political%20writer%2C%20Kagarlitsky%20was%20arrested%20on%20July%2025%20for%20'acts%20of%20terrorism'%20by%20the%20Vladimir%20Putin's%20government.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Ffreedom-for-boris-kagarlitsky-activists-globally-extend-support-to-jailed-russian-intellectual%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Watch%3A%20'Pakistan%20ko%20sukoon%20hoga'%20-%20Shoaib%20Akhtar%20takes%20a%20dig%20at%20India%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694850934000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-103710900%2Cimgsize-67330.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fsports%2Fcricket%2Fasia-cup%2Fwatch-shoaib-akhtar-takes-a-dig-at-india-after-defeat-vs-bangladesh-asia-cup%2Farticleshow%2F103710827.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Even%20though%20Shubman%20Gill%20showcased%20his%20brilliance%20with%20a%20stunning%20121%2C%20India%20experienced%20a%20close-fought%2C%20six-run%20loss%20to%20Bangladesh%20in%20a%20relatively%20unimportant%20%26quot%3BSuper%204%26quot%3B%20match%20of%20the%20Asia%20Cup%20held%20at%20the%20R%20Premadasa%20Stadium%20in%20Colombo%20on%20Friday.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20SPORTS%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A18%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fsports%2Fcricket%2Fasia-cup%2Fwatch-shoaib-akhtar-takes-a-dig-at-india-after-defeat-vs-bangladesh-asia-cup%2Farticleshow%2F103710827.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Corner%20Credit%2C%20Deflect%20Blame!%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F14000534%2F1600px-Prime_Minister_of_India_Narendra_Modi_at_an_informal_meeting_of_heads_of_state_and_government_of_the_BRICS_countries_Hamburg_2017.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20let%E2%80%99s%20set%20the%20record%20straight.%20As%20so%20compellingly%20argued%20by%20a%20friend%20in%20a%20recent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fblogs%2Fcourts-commerce-and-the-constitution%2Fchandrayaan-3-the-apogee-of-the-nehruvian-science-and-technology-model%2F%3Fsource%3Dapp%26frmapp%3Dyes%5C%22%3Earticle%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20historic%20Chandrayaan-3%20accomplishment%20is%20the%20culmination%20of%20the%20Nehruvian%20science%20and%20technology%20vision.%20The%20nurturing%20of%20the%20scientific%20temper%2C%20the%20creation%20of%20the%20iconic%20Indian%20Institutes%20of%20Technology%2C%20the%20induction%20of%20titans%20like%20Homi%20J.%20Bhabha%20and%20Vikram%20Sarabhai%20to%20spearhead%20the%20Space%20project%2C%20the%20setting%20up%20of%20the%20Indian%20Space%20Research%20Organisation%20(ISRO)%20are%20irrefutable%20affirmations%20that%20Nehru%20was%20the%20founding%20father%20and%20architect%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20space%20and%20atomic%20research%20programme.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPredictably%2C%20this%20regime%20has%20sought%20to%20make%20light%20of%20his%20role%20with%20the%20most%20outlandish%20arguments.%20The%20Donald%20Trump%20among%20TV%20anchors%20%E2%80%93%20Arnab%20Goswami%20%E2%80%93%20mockingly%20stated%20(backed%20by%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20spokesperson%E2%80%99s%20approving%20cackle)%20that%20crediting%20Nehru%20for%20our%20phenomenal%20outer%20space%20achievements%20was%20akin%20to%20acclaiming%20Abraham%20Lincoln%20for%20Neil%20Armstrong%E2%80%99s%20moon%20walk.%20To%20parody%20Dryden%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20rest%20to%20some%20faint%20meaning%20make%20pretence%2C%20but%20AG%20never%20deviates%20into%20sense.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20happier%20times%20when%20we%20were%20optimistic%20about%20our%20democracy%20and%20freedom%2C%20I%20would%20have%20roared%20with%20laughter%20at%20the%20absurd%20sight%20that%20the%20world%20witnessed%20at%20the%20precise%20point%20when%20Chandrayaan-3%20was%20making%20the%20stunning%20soft%20landing%20on%20the%20moon%20on%20August%2023%2C%20a%20red-letter%20day%20for%20a%20joyous%20nation.%20Instead%2C%20what%20I%20saw%20filled%20me%20with%20resentment%20and%20rage.%20Living%20as%20we%20are%20in%20the%20worst%20of%20times%20under%20a%20repressive%20regime%2C%20we%20have%20forgotten%20how%20to%20laugh%20or%20even%20to%20recognise%20foolishness.%20The%20ridiculous%20behaviour%20of%20a%20political%20leader%20is%20no%20longer%20seen%20for%20what%20it%20is%20%E2%80%93%20a%20stupidity%20that%20provokes%20derisive%20laughter%20%E2%80%93%20but%2C%20as%20happened%20in%20the%20case%20in%20point%2C%20is%20viewed%20with%20almost%20religious%20adoration%20by%20zillions%20of%20%3Cem%3Ebhakts%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20while%20the%20naysayers%20choke%20with%20impotent%20fury%2C%20like%20I%20did.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20refer%20to%20the%20vulgar%20juxtaposition%20of%20the%20prime%20minister%E2%80%99s%20virtual%20visage%20basking%20in%20reflected%20glory%20framed%20alongside%20Chandrayaan-3%20as%20it%20landed%20on%20the%20moon.%20This%20may%20be%20apocryphal%2C%20but%20a%20friend%20swears%20he%20heard%20one%20of%20the%20televising%20crew%20yell%3A%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3EIsko%20kyon%3F%20%3C%2Fem%3EScientists%20%3Cem%3Eko%20dikhao%3C%2Fem%3E%20(Why%20him%3F%20Let%E2%80%99s%20see%20the%20scientists).%E2%80%9D%20It%20was%20farcical%20to%20see%20the%20preening%20showman%20waving%20a%20miniscule%20flag%20in%20celebration%20of%20an%20astonishing%20achievement%2C%20usurping%20the%20limelight%20that%20rightfully%20belonged%20to%20the%20scientists.%20After%20the%20heartbreak%20of%20Chandrayaan-2%2C%20they%20deserved%20to%20be%20the%20cynosure%20of%20all%20eyes%20but%20that%E2%80%99s%20asking%20for%20the%20moon%20in%20a%20country%20where%20cult%20worship%20has%20eclipsed%20even%20the%20moon%20landing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20travesty%20did%20not%20end%20there.%20On%20his%20return%20from%20South%20Africa%20three%20days%20after%20the%20moon%20landing%2C%20the%20prime%20minister%20put%20up%20a%20show%20for%20the%20nation%20at%20the%20Delhi%20airport%2C%20shedding%20tears%20in%20an%20emotional%20outburst%20that%20was%20delayed%20for%20the%20benefit%20of%20his%20countrymen.%20He%20expressed%20his%20gratitude%20to%20the%20ISRO%20scientists%2C%20flew%20down%20to%20Bengaluru%20to%20meet%20them%20%E2%80%93%20the%20lead%20artiste%20meeting%20up%20with%20his%20facilitators%20as%20the%20television%20cameras%20whirred.%20It%20was%20an%20altogether%20command%20performance%20where%20he%20stole%20the%20thunder%20from%20Chandrayaan%20and%20the%20scientists.%20He%20did%20what%20he%20did%20with%20the%20singular%20objective%20of%20boosting%20his%20own%20image%20as%20one%20who%20leads%20from%20the%20front%2C%20the%20inspirational%20leader%20behind%20the%20Chandrayaan%20venture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fnarendra-modis-personality-has-no-place-for-compromise-or-repentance%5C%22%3ENarendra%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20Personality%20Has%20No%20Place%20for%20Compromise%20or%20Repentance%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20is%20not%20the%20only%20political%20leader%20who%20has%20ridden%20piggyback%20on%20the%20achievements%20of%20his%20fellow%20citizens.%20On%20July%2020%2C%201969%2C%20Apollo%2011%20landed%20on%20the%20moon%2C%20and%20an%20awe-struck%20world%20watched%20Neil%20Armstrong%20and%20Buzz%20Aldrin%20as%20they%20%E2%80%9Ctook%20the%20giant%20leap%20for%20mankind%E2%80%9D%20on%20the%20lunar%20orb.%20Within%20minutes%2C%20the%20infamous%20President%20Richard%20Nixon%2C%20whose%20contribution%20to%20the%20Apollo%20mission%E2%80%99s%20success%20was%20negligible%2C%20made%20a%20split-screen%20appearance%20with%20a%20live%20feed%20from%20the%20moon%2C%20and%20chatted%20with%20the%20astronauts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDetermined%20to%20use%20the%20lunar%20landing%20to%20boost%20his%20own%20reputation%2C%20Nixon%20even%20had%20his%20signature%20(along%20with%20those%20of%20the%20astronauts)%20on%20the%20plaque%20affixed%20on%20the%20lunar%20module%20which%20had%20engraved%20on%20it%20the%20memorable%20never%20to%20be%20forgotten%20message%3A%20%E2%80%9CWe%20came%20in%20peace%20for%20all%20mankind.%E2%80%9D%20(Contrast%20this%20with%20the%20sectarian%2C%20religion-tainted%20term%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%98Shiv%20Shakti%20Point%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20approved%20by%20this%20regime%20for%20the%20spot%20on%20the%20moon%E2%80%99s%20south%20pole%20where%20Chandrayaan-3%20made%20its%20historical%20landing.)%20But%20the%20American%20media%2C%20unlike%20the%20lickspittle%20back%20home%2C%20ensured%20that%20Americans%20never%20forgot%20that%20the%20Apollo%2011%20mission%20was%20set%20in%20motion%20by%20John%20F.%20Kennedy%20and%20brought%20to%20fruition%20by%20Lyndon%20Johnson.%20Nobody%20was%20fooled%20by%20Nixon%E2%80%99s%20attempt%20to%20hog%20the%20credit%20for%20the%20success%20of%20the%20Apollo%20mission.%20But%20here%2C%20the%20cult%20leader%20has%20stolen%20the%20thunder%2C%20with%20speculation%20rife%20that%20the%20Chandrayaan-3%20success%20has%20considerably%20boosted%20his%20prospects%20for%20the%202024%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20irony%20is%20that%20while%20the%20prime%20minister%20poses%20as%20a%20tech-savvy%20leader%2C%20every%20now%20and%20then%20the%20fa%C3%A7ade%20slips%2C%20revealing%20a%20hardened%20Hindu%20nationalist%20who%20has%20muddled%20up%20myth%20with%20science.%20He%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2014%2Foct%2F28%2Findian-prime-minister-genetic-science-existed-ancient-times%5C%22%3Ehas%20publicly%20affirmed%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20cosmetic%20surgery%20and%20reproductive%20genetics%20were%20practised%20in%20ancient%20India%2C%20and%20that%20Lord%20Ram%20flew%20the%20first%20aeroplane.%20His%20unscientific%20simple-mindedness%20became%20public%20knowledge%20when%20he%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fcontroversy-over-pm-narendra-modis-cloud-can-help-us-escape-radar-comment-on-balakot-air-strikes-2036402%5C%22%3Esuggested%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20clouds%20would%20prevent%20Pakistani%20radars%20from%20detecting%20Indian%20fighter%20jets%20during%20the%20Balakot%20air%20strike.%20Apart%20from%20its%20sheer%20absurdity%2C%20his%20statement%20was%20made%20with%20the%20clear%20intent%20of%20taking%20credit%20for%20strategising%20the%20successful%20air%20strike%2C%20but%20it%20boomeranged.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMuch%20more%20troubling%20is%20his%20regime%E2%80%99s%20tampering%20with%20the%20study%20of%20science%20at%20the%20school%20level%2C%20reflected%20in%20the%20recent%20retrograde%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fncert-drops-chapters-on-periodic-table-challenges-to-democracy-from-class-10-textbooks%5C%22%3Emove%20by%20the%20NCERT%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20remove%20the%20periodic%20table%2C%20Darwin%E2%80%99s%20theory%2C%20electromagnetism%20and%20the%20sustainable%20use%20of%20natural%20resources%20from%20school%20textbooks.%20In%20the%20inhospitable%20environment%20of%20Hindutva-fuelled%20mythical%20science%2C%20one%20wonders%20if%20we%20will%20be%20able%20to%20sustain%20the%20level%20of%20excellence%20that%20saw%20us%20to%20the%20moon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPrime%20Minister%20Modi%20has%20made%20a%20habit%20of%20breaking%20down%20in%20public.%20In%202015%2C%20he%20choked%20up%20when%20talking%20about%20his%20mother%20to%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%20in%20a%20Town%20Hall%20discussion%20and%20brought%20up%20the%20scarcely%20credible%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Farticle%2Fnews-ians%2Fdespite-lie-allegation-modi-says-mother-washed-utensils-116041400881_1.html%5C%22%3Estory%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20his%20mother%20washing%20utensils%20at%20the%20homes%20of%20his%20neighbours%20to%20raise%20him.%20Following%20the%20demonetisation%20disaster%20in%202016%2C%20he%20used%20emotional%20blackmail%2C%20tear%20ducts%20leaking%20as%20he%20pleaded%20with%20his%20countrymen%20for%2050%20days%20to%20set%20matters%20right%2C%20irrelevantly%20claiming%20to%20be%20a%20martyr%3A%20%E2%80%9CI%E2%80%99m%20not%20here%20for%20the%20%3Cem%3Ekursi.%20%3C%2Fem%3EI%20left%20my%20home%2C%20family%2C%20everything%20for%20the%20country%E2%80%9D%3B%20also%20alluding%20darkly%20to%20powers%20who%20%E2%80%9Cwill%20not%20let%20me%20live.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20it%20was%20about%20himself.%20Even%20an%20inconsequential%20non-event%20like%20the%20farewell%20to%20Ghulam%20Nabi%20Azad%20in%202021%20on%20completion%20of%20his%20tenure%20as%20Rajya%20Sabha%20member%20provoked%20a%20display%20of%20tear-filled%20histrionics%20from%20the%20prime%20minister%2C%20the%20self-indulgent%20sentimentalist%20nonpareil!%20But%20the%20searing%20human%20suffering%20in%20Manipur%20and%20Nuh%20has%20left%20him%20unmoved.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fnarendra-modi-talked-about-the-manipur-violence-but-did-he-really%5C%22%3ENarendra%20Modi%20Talked%20About%20the%20Manipur%20Violence.%20But%20Did%20He%20Really%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20emotional%20outbursts%20are%20clearly%20well%20thought-out%2C%20a%20strategy%20to%20win%20sympathy%20and%20the%20hearts%20of%20people%20with%20a%20show%20of%20his%20sensitivity%2C%20caring%20and%20sheer%20humaneness.%C2%A0%20Whenever%20confronted%20by%20one%20of%20his%20sentimental%20moments%2C%20I%20am%20reminded%20of%20James%20Baldwin%E2%80%99s%20warning%20about%20such%20fake%20heart-on-sleeve%20characters%3A%20%E2%80%9CSentimentality%2C%20the%20ostentatious%20parading%20of%20excessive%20and%20spurious%20emotion%2C%20is%20the%20mark%20of%20dishonesty%E2%80%A6the%20wet%20eyes%20of%20the%20sentimentalist%20betray%E2%80%A6%20his%20fear%20of%20life%2C%20his%20arid%20heart%3B%20and%20it%20is%20always%2C%20therefore%20the%20signal%20of%20secret%20and%20violent%20inhumanity%2C%20the%20mark%20of%20cruelty.%E2%80%9D%20Baldwin%20has%20helped%20us%20understand%20our%20man%20and%20his%20playacting!%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20entire%20career%20is%20a%20validation%20of%20Baldwin%E2%80%99s%20forensic%20diagnosis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20know%20in%20our%20bones%20that%20a%20good%20leader%20takes%20responsibility%20for%20failures%20and%20gives%20credit%20to%20others%20for%20success%2C%20but%20that%E2%80%99s%20not%20our%20Supreme%20Leader%E2%80%99s%20style.%20He%20is%20all%20over%20the%20map%20in%20good%20times%2C%20hosting%20medal-winning%20Olympic%20athletes%20or%20inaugurating%20every%20project%2C%20bar%20none%20or%20elbowing%20out%20scientists.%20But%20in%20bad%20times%2C%20he%20either%20ducks%20or%20maintains%20an%20Olympian%20silence%2C%20as%20he%20did%20during%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.telegraphindia.com%2Fopinion%2Fall-quiet-on-covid-19-second-wave%2Fcid%2F1813922%5C%22%3Esecond%20COVID-19%20wave%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20prolonged%20trauma%20following%20demonetisation%2C%20the%20shameful%20Brij%20Bhushan%20saga%2C%20and%20continues%20to%20do%20regarding%20Manipur%2C%20Nuh%2C%20the%20Adani%20scam%20and%20the%20Chinese%20occupation%20of%20our%20land.%20And%20of%20course%2C%20he%20employs%20another%20ruse%20%E2%80%93%20blames%20Nehru%20for%20some%20of%20the%20mess%20we%20are%20currently%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20what%20is%20to%20be%20done%20when%20a%20cult%20leader%20has%20his%20legions%20of%20followers%20in%20thrall%2C%20creating%20an%20emotional%20bond%20and%20undying%20faith%20that%20are%20steadfast%20even%20when%20their%20leader%E2%80%99s%20actions%20harm%20them%20grievously%3F%20What%20can%20anybody%20do%20about%20the%20irrational%2C%20blind%20%3Cem%3EBhakti%20of%20%3C%2Fem%3Ea%20leader%20intent%20on%20splitting%20up%20Bharat%20and%20India%20to%20hold%20on%20to%20power%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20writer%20is%20a%20former%20civil%20servant.%20The%20views%20are%20personal.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694850512000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F14000534%2F1600px-Prime_Minister_of_India_Narendra_Modi_at_an_informal_meeting_of_heads_of_state_and_government_of_the_BRICS_countries_Hamburg_2017.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fcorner-credit-deflect-blame%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22It%E2%80%99s%20not%20about%20his%20people%3B%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20about%20his%20alma%20mater%3B%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20about%20his%20party%3B%20it%E2%80%99s%20all%20about%20himself.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%