aal%E2%80%99%2C%20or%20Will%20Food%20Inflation%20Decide%20the%20Elections%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F04%2F08200712%2FScreen-Shot-2020-04-08-at-8.06.53-PM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theindiacable.com%2Fp%2Fec-bill-downgrades-election-commissioners%5C%22%3Ewas%20first%20published%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0on%20The%20India%20Cable%C2%A0%E2%80%93%20a%20premium%20newsletter%20from%20The%20Wire%20%26amp%3B%20Galileo%20Ideas%20%E2%80%93%20and%20has%20been%20republished%20here.%20To%20subscribe%20to%20The%20India%20Cable%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theindiacable.com%2F%5C%22%3Eclick%20here%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStickiness%20in%20food%20inflation%20had%20made%20the%20UPA%20government%20unpopular%20back%20in%202013.%20Double-digit%20food%20inflation%20was%20hurting%20the%20poor%20and%20the%20Opposition%20had%20begun%20to%20taunt%20former%20Prime%20Minister%20Manmohan%20Singh%20for%20his%20failure%2C%20especially%20since%20he%20is%20an%20eminent%20economist%2C%20to%20control%20food%20prices.%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20is%20no%20economist%20but%20he%20has%20boasted%20in%20the%20past%20that%20his%20government%20does%20better%20than%20Manmohan%20Singh%20on%20inflation.%20But%20Modi%20was%20blessed%20with%20falling%20oil%2C%20food%20and%20metal%20prices%20in%20the%20years%20after%202014%2C%20which%20moderated%20overall%20inflation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20honeymoon%20with%20low%20to%20moderate%20inflation%20is%20all%20but%20over%20and%20the%20stickiness%20in%20food%20inflation%20is%20worrying%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20a%20great%20deal%20as%20several%20state%20elections%20draw%20closer%2C%20along%20with%20the%20general%20elections%20next%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJust%20as%20food%20inflation%20had%20peaked%20in%20the%20second%20half%20of%202013%2C%20the%20trend%20appears%20to%20be%20repeating%20in%202023.%20July%20and%20August%20have%20seen%20double-digit%20food%20inflation%2C%20as%20India%20suffered%20an%2011%25%20monsoon%20deficit%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20eight%20years.%20Inflationary%20expectations%20are%20clearly%20on%20the%20rise%2C%20as%20the%20government%20imposes%20export%20curbs%20on%20a%20range%20of%20food%20items.%20Prices%20of%20milk%2C%20pulses%20and%20edible%20oil%20have%20generally%20been%20structurally%20on%20the%20higher%20side%20for%20quite%20some%20time%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIndeed%2C%20if%20food%20inflation%20proves%20to%20be%20sticky%20in%20the%20months%20ahead%2C%20it%20will%20raise%20political%20headwinds%20for%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%20and%20the%20BJP%20during%20the%20crucial%20assembly%20elections%20in%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20Rajasthan%2C%20Telangana%20and%20Chhattisgarh.%20The%20BJP%20knows%20that%20high%20energy%20prices%2C%20especially%20that%20of%20cooking%20gas%2C%20hurt%20the%20party%20badly%20in%20Karnataka%2C%20and%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Flpg-price-cut-modis-rakhi-gift-ends-up-drawing-attention-to-inflation%5C%22%3Ecut%20LPG%20prices%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20Rs%20200%20recently.%20But%20prices%20of%20LPG%2C%20diesel%20and%20petrol%20remain%20quite%20high.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20inflationary%20expectations%20build%20up%20in%20the%20economy%2C%20it%20is%20very%20difficult%20to%20put%20the%20genie%20back%20in%20the%20bottle.%20The%20Ukraine%20war%20had%20created%20the%20first%20round%20of%20very%20high%20inflationary%20expectations%20last%20year.%20Both%20food%20and%20energy%20prices%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.imf.org%2Fen%2FBlogs%2FArticles%2F2022%2F12%2F09%2Fglobal-food-prices-to-remain-elevated-amid-war-costly-energy-la-nina%5C%22%3Esoared%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20there%20was%20an%20unprecedented%20spike%20in%20global%20inflation.%20The%20advanced%20economies%20were%20hit%20hard%20and%20are%20still%20grappling%20with%20high%20inflation%20via%20blunt%20monetary%20policy%20tools.%20It%20may%20take%20a%20while%20for%20global%20inflation%20to%20flag%20and%20India%20cannot%20escape%20the%20overall%20trend%20of%20higher%20inflation%20and%20lower%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20there%20seems%20to%20be%20some%20recovery%20(contested%20by%20economists%20like%20Ashoka%20Mody)%20in%20the%20April-June%20quarter%2C%20the%20reality%20is%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%20GDP%20has%20grown%20annually%20only%20about%203.5%25%20for%20four%20years%20from%202019-20%20to%202022-23.%20So%20incomes%20have%20not%20really%20recovered%20significantly%20and%20inflationary%20expectations%20are%20getting%20entrenched%20even%20before%20a%20full%20recovery%20is%20underway.%20There%20is%20ample%20evidence%20from%20consumption%20patterns%20that%20the%20bottom%2070%25%20of%20the%20population%2C%20whose%20incomes%20were%20hit%20badly%20by%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%2C%20have%20not%20recovered%20yet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20September%2015%2C%20Mallikarjun%20Kharge%20told%20the%20prime%20minister%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2Fredirect%2F6b8472bd-6f83-4d2b-be0a-f5a9ea5f5a32%3Fj%3DeyJ1IjoiaHpuMnUifQ.MQOquijPBw98XVYBc9m195DW7Qx9ruSvngQYE7EwHGg%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2Fredirect%2F6b8472bd-6f83-4d2b-be0a-f5a9ea5f5a32%3Fj%253DeyJ1IjoiaHpuMnUifQ.MQOquijPBw98XVYBc9m195DW7Qx9ruSvngQYE7EwHGg%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1694926238549000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw35hMbWYBgVYab32NZPm15e%5C%22%3Estop%20diversionary%20tactics%20and%20focus%20on%20inflation%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20because%20the%2020%25%20poorest%20Indians%20are%20bearing%20the%20brunt%20of%20the%20problem%2C%20brought%20on%20by%20the%20%E2%80%9Cgrand%20loot%E2%80%9D%20conducted%20by%20his%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20nationwide%20survey%20by%20the%20Centre%20for%20Monitoring%20Indian%20Economy%20shows%20that%20people%20expect%20prices%20to%20remain%20high%20and%20even%20their%20expectation%20of%20future%20income%20growth%20is%20relatively%20low.%20This%20reflects%20the%20broader%20sentiment%2C%20even%20as%20self-congratulatory%20claims%20of%20India%20being%20a%20beacon%20of%20global%20growth%20abound.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20can%E2%80%99t%20help%20but%20feel%20that%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%2C%20heady%20with%20the%20G20%20success%2C%20is%20in%20a%20mood%20to%20launch%20a%20campaign%20like%20India%20Shining%2C%20which%20his%20mentor%20L.K.%20Advani%20had%20unleashed%20in%202003%20on%20the%20back%20of%20an%20incipient%20economic%20recovery.%20Is%20the%20BJP%20again%20creating%20a%20bubble%20via%20its%20own%20self-seeking%20narrative%3F%20Of%20course%2C%20the%20India%20of%202023%20is%20not%20the%20country%20it%20was%20in%202003.%20Today%2C%20significant%20sections%20of%20voters%20seem%20to%20be%20willing%20to%20suffer%20a%20great%20deal%20of%20hardship%20before%20the%20promised%20entry%20into%20%E2%80%98Amrit%20Kaal%E2%80%99%20(era%20of%20great%20prosperity).%20But%20equally%2C%20voters%20tend%20to%20change%20their%20minds%20overnight%2C%20and%20they%20will%20keep%20political%20parties%20on%20tenterhooks%20in%20the%20months%20ahead.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694843789000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F04%2F08200712%2FScreen-Shot-2020-04-08-at-8.06.53-PM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitical-economy%2Fwill-voters-wait-hungrily-for-amrit-kaal-or-will-food-inflation-decide-the-elections%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Prime%20Minister%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20honeymoon%20with%20low%20to%20moderate%20inflation%20is%20all%20but%20over%20and%20the%20stickiness%20in%20food%20inflation%20is%20worrying%20the%20BJP%20a%20great%20deal%20as%20several%20state%20elections%20draw%20closer%2C%20along%20with%20the%20general%20elections%20next%20year.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitical-economy%2Fwill-voters-wait-hungr